<plot>The 2004 edition of the annual Bodil Awards gave first honors for best Danish film to 'Lars von Trier' (qv)'s _Dogville (2003)_ (qv) while the four acting awards were shared by _Arven (2003)_ (qv) and _Lykkevej (2003)_ (qv). The show, hosted by entertainer 'Michael Carøe' (qv) and broadcast on a three-hour delay, also saw internationally acclaimed cinematographer 'Anthony Dod Mantle' (qv) take home a diploma for his work, while director 'Anders Refn' (qv) received the honorary award.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?077578</url></doc>
